<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-06-23T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-06-23T14:00:00-05:00" n="902" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d902">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/590: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-23T15:00:00-04:00">June 23,
                                    1942—3 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>294. Your 653, June 22, 1 p.m. and 655, June 22. The following telegram
                            has been sent to Cairo.</p>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“Your June 14, 5 p.m. to Ankara. General Arnold is instructing
                                Colonel Halverson that disposition of planes and personnel in Turkey
                                is now a subject of diplomatic negotiations being conducted by the
                                State Department and that no military official should proceed to
                                Turkey in connection with the matter.</p>
                            <p>Repeated to Ankara.”</p>
                        </quote>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>